# Grocery Store

A simple example including table scripting to perform a photo update and a progress bar added to any new task

### Source code

```html
<html>
  <script src="https://bossanova.uk/jspreadsheet/v4/jspreadsheet.js"></script>
  <script src="https://jsuites.net/v5/jsuites.js"></script>
  <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@jspreadsheet/formula/dist/index.min.js"></script>
  <link
    rel="stylesheet"
    href="https://bossanova.uk/jspreadsheet/v4/jspreadsheet.css"
    type="text/css"
  />
  <link
    rel="stylesheet"
    href="https://jsuites.net/v5/jsuites.css"
    type="text/css"
  />

  <div id="spreadsheet"></div>

  <script>
    let data = [
      [
        "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
        "Vegetables",
        "Carrots",
        "2019-02-12",
        "14.00",
        "4",
        "=RATING(F1)",
      ],
      [
        "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
        "Fruits",
        "Apple",
        "2019-03-01",
        "45.00",
        "5",
        "=RATING(F2)",
      ],
      [
        "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
        "Fruits",
        "Pinapples",
        "2018-11-10",
        "30.00",
        "4",
        "=RATING(F3)",
      ],
      [
        "data:image/jpeg;base64,",
        "Fruits",
        "Plums",
        "2019-01-12",
        "14.00",
        "4",
        "=RATING(F4)",
      ],
    ];

    // A custom method to create RATING stars html based on a number
    let RATING = function (rating) {
      let fullStar = `<span style="color: yellow; font-size: 15px;">&#9733;</span>`; // Filled star
      let emptyStar = `<span style="color: gray; font-size: 15px;">&#9733;</span>`; // Empty star

      let starRatingHtml = "";

      // Add filled stars
      for (let i = 0; i < Math.floor(rating); i++) {
        starRatingHtml += fullStar;
      }

      // Add empty stars
      for (let i = Math.floor(rating); i < 5; i++) {
        starRatingHtml += emptyStar;
      }

      return starRatingHtml;
    };

    formula.setFormula({ RATING });

    let table = jspreadsheet(document.getElementById("spreadsheet"), {
      data: data,
      search: true,
      pagination: 10,
      paginationOptions: [10, 25, 50],
      columns: [
        { type: "image", width: "110px", title: "Photo" },
        {
          type: "dropdown",
          width: "120px",
          title: "Category",
          source: [
            "Vegetables",
            "Fruits",
            "Grains, Beans and Nuts",
            "Meat and Poultry",
            "Fish and Seafood",
            "Dairy Foods",
          ],
        },
        { type: "text", width: "150px", title: "Description" },
        { type: "calendar", width: "100px", title: "Best before" },
        { type: "text", width: "80px", title: "Price", mask: "$ #,##" },
        { type: "text", width: "50px", title: "Score" },
        { type: "text", width: "100px", title: "Rating", stripHTML: false },
      ],
      updateTable: function (instance, cell, col, row, val, label, cellName) {
        if (col == 5 && !val) {
          instance.jexcel.setValue("F" + (row + 1), "=RATING(E" + (row + 1));
        }
      },
    });
  </script>
</html>
```
